radiographic_examinations.findings: Unremarkable lung bases and cardiac apex; a 7 mm segment V liver hypodensity possibly representing a hemangioma. Normal spleen, bilateral adrenals, left kidney, pancreas. A subcentimeter hypodensity in the right kidney. Abdominal aorta normal in course and caliber. Unremarkable small and large bowel. Blind-ending fluid-filled tubular structure in a retrocecal area with a hyperemic wall measuring 1 cm, concerning for retrocecal appendicitis. Unremarkable bladder, prostate, and rectum. Scrotal wall thickening observed.
